  "body": "# Follow up\r\n\r\na follow up issue for this PR #18118, there is an issue with avatar status indicator when we scale it down while user scroll the screen. \r\n\r\nand it's related to this design review comment [Figma link](https://www.figma.com/file/Tf5nfkYvpbnNCo4rKLK7lS?node-id=8179:42854&mode=design#649968437)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nWhen user scroll down and we scale down the avatar, status indicator should match design. \r\n\r\nInitial ---> After Scroll\r\n<div>\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/71308738/180b86c6-1164-4090-8436-d1e0f787bf58\" width=\"390px\"/>\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/71308738/798d9538-02b3-4525-b50b-e243a8e08b54\" width=\"390px\"/>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n## Technical description\r\nIt appears that the entire avatar, along with its status indicator, is treated as a single image. While we utilize Reanimated to scale the avatar up and down during scrolling, it's essential to note that the status indicator should only resize to specific sizes (from 12 to 8).\r\n\r\n\r\n",
